Unilateral motor control. Visually guided reaching (VGR) path length ratio (PLR z-scores) and movement time (MT z-scores). A Mean VGR PLR z-score plotted as a function of feedback group (Aug. PF = Augmented position sense feedback, VF = visual feedback only) and time (Baseline versus 24-h Post-test). Error bars represent 95% confidence intervals. B Mean change in in PLR z-score (24-h Post-test – Baseline) plotted relative to the MDC90 threshold (1.29). C Mean VGR MT z-score plotted as a function of feedback group and time (Baseline versus 24-h Post-test. Error bars represent 95% confidence intervals. D Mean change in MT z-score (24 hour Post-test – Baseline) plotted relative to the MDC90 threshold (0.92). Negative change scores represent improvement for each motor control parameter. Group means are represented by shaded bars. Individuals subject scores are represented by individual points on the plot, disaggregated by established cut-offs for severe, moderate, and mild upper limb motor impairment defined by Fugl-Meyer score [49].

